@arthurvane3901 
North Vietnam's supplies were not endless. Soviet and Chinese aid to North Vietnam was only about 10% or less compared to American aid to the Republic of Vietnam. North Vietnam even refused to accept Chinese drivers. 
The conflict between the Soviet Union and China put Vietnam at a disadvantage. Soviet aid through China was cut or changed in quality. What could North Vietnam "take advantage of" in this situation?

@RealGurt1​⁠​⁠ I know that this is a long-standing American term so I don't care much, but then you think Vietnamese people are arrogant when they want to bring a more correct view of the truth of war? 
We respect history and want it to be recognized correctly. The name  “Vietnam war” means a civil war, that the two regions of North and South Vietnam fought each other, the truth is that the US army jumped into Vietnam, dropped more than 15 million tons of bombs, k*lled millions of people. The war has been over for decades, we have risen and changed but never forget history, even more hate the act of swapping history, color revolution…
So, sorry if the reaction of many Vietnamese people makes you uncomfortable but the truth is that Vietnamese people are very serious about historical issues, we have every right to be proud of our victory and have the right to express our views on a documentary related to our history.

